               <head>Grant; Needham Street; 1327</head>
               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111667">Needham Street (Needham-Street)</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1327">1327</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Persoun</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>
                        </persName> to <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Priour</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gayslee)</placeName>
                        </persName>, <persName nymRef="Priour">
                           <forename>Petronilla</forename> his wife</persName>, and <persName nymRef="Priour">
                           <forename>John</forename> their son</persName>, of a piece of arable land, in the croft of the said Walter persoun, and next to the land of the said Walter Priour with one and abutting on the land of the <orgName key="org_105030">prior and convent of Stokes</orgName> and in width one perch.
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>, on Monday the feast of St Thomas Apostle, 1 Edw. III [21 Dec, 1327]
                        Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Inercer</surname>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> of <surname>Hapetone</surname>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Sperlyng</surname>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Dersoun</surname>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Aumener</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>
                        </persName>, and others. 
                     The seal is wanting.
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
